696-# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
697-# Helper: start a GPU monitor background process.
698-# Identical to _bg_start but adds --gpus-per-node=<n> to the remote srun
699-# step so SLURM's GPU cgroup gives the monitor process access to the GPU
700:# device files (without this, pynvml queries return None on remote nodes).
701-#
702-# Root cause of empty monitor CSVs on remote nodes:
703-#   SLURM enforces GPU device cgroup isolation per step.  A step with no
704-#   GPU GRES request gets an empty device cgroup → /dev/nvidia* not
705:#   accessible → NVML returns errors for all device queries → None values.
706-#   --overlap allows the monitor step to share the GPUs already claimed by
707-#   the vLLM server step without triggering "nodes are busy".
708-#
709-# Usage: _bg_start_mon <node> <array_name> <n_gpus> <command...>
